The paper discusses the limits of open peer-to-peer networks and permissionless blockchain networks in terms of system complexity, security, instability, and performance. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category, as well as the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper reviews research on distributed systems, which could place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for cooperation between entities, which could relate to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
